</table><para id="fs-idm357754512">For example, the production cost pool consists of costs such as indirect labor for those accepting the order, verifying the customer has credit to pay for the order, maintenance and depreciation on the machines used to produce the orders, and utilities and rent for operating the machines. <link target-id="OSX_Acct_M06_03_CostPools"/> illustrates how the costs in each pool are allocated to each product in a different proportion.</para>
<figure id="OSX_Acct_M06_03_CostPools">
